<div class="stackedit__html"><h1 id="adding-social-share-buttons-to-your-website">Adding Social share buttons to your website</h1>
<h3 id="scenario">Scenario</h3>
<p>Social share buttons encourage users to link to your website from their profile on various social media platforms.</p>
<h3 id="solution">Solution</h3>
<p>Adding a social share button requires the following steps:</p>
<ol>
<li>Figure out the sharer link</li>
<li>Obtain svg graphic of sharer icon</li>
<li>Create an anchor tag with above sharer link and icon</li>
<li>Test share</li>
</ol>
<p>Sharer link and sharer icon for various social media platforms are listed below.</p>
<h4 id="facebook">Facebook</h4>
<pre><code>https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?caption=${post_caption}&amp;u={url}
</code></pre>
<p>You can use the below svg code to get the facebook button icon <sub><svg id="facebook_social_icon" viewBox="0 0 18 18" width="30px" fill="#3b5998"><br></br>
<path d="M15.7,1.5H2.3c-0.5,0-0.8,0.4-0.8,0.8v13.3c0,0.5,0.4,0.8,0.8,0.8h7.2v-5.8h-2V8.4h2V6.8c0-1.9,1.2-3,2.9-3 c0.8,0,1.5,0.1,1.7,0.1v2l-1.2,0c-0.9,0-1.1,0.4-1.1,1.1v1.4h2.2l-0.3,2.3h-1.9v5.8h3.8c0.5,0,0.8-0.4,0.8-0.8V2.3 C16.5,1.9,16.1,1.5,15.7,1.5z"><br></br>
</path><br></br>
</svg></sub></p>
